g.text: Railing: Someone has left an unidentifiable article of clothing on this railing. It smells really bad.
Conceptualization: A poet could write a dozen verses and still not begin to capture the profound vexation in that sigh.
You: "It could have been multiple seagulls."
Inland Empire: This jacket reeks of loss and failure. It could be the one that the idiot in the colourful tracksuit was looking for...
Logic: It seems likely that it was left in the surf until someone laid it out on this fence to dry out. Unfortunately that just seems to have stiffened it into a shapeless mass.
Kim Kitsuragi: "A clue? You think our suspect is a seagull who's been defecating on unsuspecting jackets?"
Railing: It's streaked with dried seagull shit and tangled with pieces of seaweed. A dangling arm suggests that there might be a jacket beneath the crust of filth.
Railing: The cloth, if you can still call it that, makes a soft crunching sound as you thrust your finger into it.
Interfacing: You should still take it.
Interfacing: Much as the thought of touching it causes you to cringe, this could be the jacket that the idiot in the colourful tracksuit was looking for...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Please tell me you're not taking that with you."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's a guano-encrusted jacket. And you're already carrying around enough as it is."
Interfacing: You should still take it. It's probably Doom Spiral's.
You: "I think this is the jacket the Idiot Doom Spiral Guy wanted me to find."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant looks at the stinking rag and sniffs. "I'm sure he'll be *thrilled* to have it returned."
